# Memory hygiene

- Store stable preferences and long-lived constraints.
- Avoid secrets/PII and ephemeral details.
- Separate:
  - workflow state (structured, checkpointed)
  - long-term memory (curated, user-controlled)
- Retrieve memory only when triggered by intent or explicit need.
